        <form action="/login" method="post">
            Username: <input type="text" name="username"><br>
            Password: <input type="password" name="password"><br>
            <input type="submit" value="Login">
        </form>
    '''

if __name__ == '__main__':
    app.run(debug=True)
```

This example uses Flask to create a simple web application. The `/login` route handles both GET and POST requests for logging in. If the login credentials are correct, the user is redirected to the main page (`/`). Otherwise, the user is prompted to enter their credentials.

